news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement's net profit up 17.73% in Q3 FY23
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,576.06 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 20.88 per cent from Rs 1,303.81 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: New developing areas to get over 3,500 LED streetlights in Nashik
news.para: Of the 3,500 LED streetlights, 40% will be installed in developing areas on the outskirts of Panchavati and Satpur divisions. The Nashik Municipal Corporation officials said that new residential areas are coming up on the outskirts of Nashik city.

news.title: Puravankara posts net profit of Rs 22.55 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Puravankara's consolidated total income stood at Rs 410.40 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 66.52 per cent from Rs 246.45 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso: No decision on payout for families who were forced to abandon homes
news.para: Tower D cannot be demolished before settling the claims of flat owners, for which a time of 60 days was defined when the order to raze the tower was issued.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body will cut UGD line for property tax defaulters
news.para: If defaulters continue to skip paying taxes, the HDMC will take measures to disconnect the UGD connection of their houses. From Thursday onwards, HDMC officials have started tough measures in the city to improve the revenue of the corporation.

news.title: Parliamentary panel asks Centre to raise financial assistance for PMAY-Rural
news.para: The 30-member committee on estimates, headed by BJP MP Girish Bhalchandra Bapat, asked the ministry of rural development to revise the financial assistance provided to help beneficiaries in timely completion of houses sanctioned.

news.title: Of 13 lakh grievances on Dharani portal, 12 lakh resolved: Telangana housing minister
news.para: Speaking in the assembly on budget demands and grants on Thursday, he said this scheme would be implemented in addition to the 2BHK scheme. "Apart from 2.92 lakh 2BHK units, four lakh people will be benefited by the new scheme," the minister said.

news.title: Indore civic body identifies top 20 property tax defaulters
news.para: According to senior IMC officials concerned, the civic body has around Rs 750 Crore to be recovered as property tax due by end of March in this calendar year.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board cancels allotment of 22 small flats after survey
news.para: The CHB has allotted more than 18,000 flats under Rehabilitation Scheme/Small Flat Scheme/Affordable Rental Housing Scheme. The flats cannot be sold, transferred and sub-let.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: 40 years on, no headway in housing project in Chiplun
news.para: Under the agreed 40:60 formula, 40 per cent of the developed land was to be returned to the farmers while Mhada was to carry out development works on their 60 per cent land. The prime land is located along the Mumbai-Goa highway.

news.title: Bombay HC quashes SRA notice to cancel 517 slum projects
news.para: ​The high court bench of Justice G S Patel and Justice S G Dige ruled that the notice which was issued was, "Entirely outside the frame of the law and not issued in accordance with law."

news.title: Punjab National Bank and Bank of Baroda raise lending rates by up to 25 bps
news.para: ​PNB in a regulatory filing said it has effected a 25 basis point increase in the Repo Linked Lending Rate (RLLR) from 8.75 per cent to 9 per cent effective from Thursday.

news.title: Mumbai: Welspun Group's chairman buys penthouse in Worli for Rs 240 crore
news.para: ​TOI has learned that B K Goenka, chairman of Welspun Group, has purchased the triplex (through a group company) in Three Sixty West, a luxury project at Annie Besant Road, Worli.

news.title: Hindalco leases 50,000 sq ft office space in Blackstone's Mumbai tower
news.para: The company will be paying total rent of nearly Rs 54 crore for these five years including a 15% rent escalation after the first 36 months. The agreement provides an option to extend the term of the lease by additional five years.

news.title: CBI kicks off probe into collapse in Gurugram's Chintels Paradiso
news.para: The team which was accompanied by police spoke to residents of the society regarding the incident and proceedings after the collapse. The team also spoke to residents about the structural audit which was conducted by IIT-Delhi.
